 spectres don't path back on the beach.  Beach-side loose spectres roam the coast killing off newbies.  If you can't do it, skip the whole kiting spectres thing.  Your need for safe xp doesn't include killing people to get it.<br>
<br>
His guild leader at first denied he was in Clan Werre (Slades was anon).  I pointed out guildstatus showed him as a member and the leader said he'd look into it.  No other responses.  Next day, I find another CW player kiting Oasis spectres on the beach.  This guy was a lot more polite and I didn't see the huge trail of dead bodies as I did with Slades.  So, I think he probably had it under control eventhough he still wouldn't move out west.  One mistake on the beach and it's not just you dead, it's half the newbies in the zone, too.  Risking your own neck is fine, but not everyone else's.<br>
<br>
I guess you could say CW /con's apprehensive to me now.  I've had buffs and good experiences with other CW, so they're not dubious or scowly.  But, I'm now always extra careful when I see one fighting in zone and the CW tag definitely has no meaning with respect to personal character or ability.  Kinda sad for CW really.  When I guild I definitely want to be part of one where people respect the tag.<br>
<br>
I've had minimal interaction with FnF &amp; Resolution (the other two high level guilds), but it's all been good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1>Firiona Vie General Chat</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href="http://www.firionavie.org/">Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  